```jsx
// Import the necessary modules
import { useRouter } from 'next/router';

// Create your functional component
const MyComponent = () => {
  // Access the router object
  const router = useRouter();

  // Access the query parameters
  const { subPId } = router.query;

  // Render your component
  return (
    <div>
      <h1>Page Slug: {subPId}</h1>
      {/* Rest of your component */}
    </div>
  );
};

export default MyComponent;
```

In this example, we import the `useRouter` hook from `next/router` to access the router object. We then destructure the `subPId` query parameter from the `router.query` object.

You can now use the `subPId` variable in your component to display the value of the `subPId` query parameter.

